08:50.784 --> 08:52.919
So Lindsay's mother took out
a second mortgage

08:52.921 --> 08:55.672
so she could send cash
to her here, but the problem is--

08:55.674 --> 08:58.892
Money doesn't go quite as far
in California as it does in Minnesota.

08:58.894 --> 09:00.393
Exactly. And Lindsay
must have known

09:00.395 --> 09:02.061
that her mother would
be worried about her,

09:02.063 --> 09:03.897
so she told her that
she found an apartment

09:03.899 --> 09:05.431
or order to relieve
the financial stress.

09:05.433 --> 09:06.900
You think she was living here?

09:06.902 --> 09:10.186
Well, they don't
charge any rent.

09:14.842 --> 09:17.277
Excuse me. We're looking
for Sarah Mapes.

09:17.279 --> 09:18.745
Who's asking?

09:18.747 --> 09:20.530
I'm Aaron Hotchner.
This is David Rossi.

09:20.532 --> 09:21.865
We're with the FBI.

09:21.867 --> 09:23.666
What do you need, Aaron?

09:23.668 --> 09:25.034
We're investigating
homicides

09:25.036 --> 09:26.836
that have taken place
in the area in the last week.

09:26.838 --> 09:30.290
They called the FBI in
over a couple of burnt bodies?

09:30.292 --> 09:31.925
What happened?

09:31.927 --> 09:34.994
One of them a doctor?

09:34.996 --> 09:38.181
One of them was
a 19-year-old girl.

09:38.183 --> 09:40.433
Lindsay.

09:40.435 --> 09:42.519
What can you tell us
about her?

09:42.521 --> 09:44.971
She comes here now and then.

09:44.973 --> 09:47.390
Always singing for everybody.

09:47.392 --> 09:51.311
Made me promise to vote for her
if she ever made it on TV.

09:53.147 --> 09:54.614
You telling me she's dead?

09:54.616 --> 09:56.282
I'm afraid so.

09:56.284 --> 09:58.234
That's a damn shame.

09:58.236 --> 09:59.619
I'll be right back.

09:59.621 --> 10:02.071
Always the young ones.

10:06.327 --> 10:09.028
Excuse me. Sir?

10:10.331 --> 10:12.916
Sergeant Scott?

10:35.856 --> 10:37.924
Lock it up, Marines!

10:37.926 --> 10:40.426
- You got a death wish, Marine?
- No, Sergeant!

10:40.428 --> 10:41.661
In that case, Private Rossi,

10:41.663 --> 10:42.929
you might want
to put your helmet on

10:42.931 --> 10:46.599
before the Viet Cong
decide to paint your face red.

10:46.601 --> 10:49.335
There's a war going on
here, marines.

10:49.337 --> 10:51.004
The sooner you start
acting like it,

10:51.006 --> 10:52.472
the sooner you start
making it to tomorrow.

10:52.474 --> 10:55.108
And you, what's
your name, Marine?

10:55.110 --> 10:56.576
Private First Class
Hernandez!

10:56.578 --> 10:59.612
Well, Private
First Class Hernandez,

10:59.614 --> 11:01.414
seems like you landed
in some sunny resort.

11:01.416 --> 11:03.249
That's the only
reason I can think

11:03.251 --> 11:05.151
why you wouldn't be wearing
your flak jacket!

11:05.153 --> 11:06.819
Sorry, Sergeant!

11:06.821 --> 11:08.187
Sorry don't cut it
out here, marines.

11:08.189 --> 11:09.789
Sorry get you dead.

11:09.791 --> 11:11.257
And if you're dead,

11:11.259 --> 11:12.492
I have to carry your ass
back here

11:12.494 --> 11:14.227
so we can mail y'all
to your mama

11:14.229 --> 11:15.361
in a big wooden box.

11:15.363 --> 11:16.729
Now, do you think
I want scoliosis?

11:16.731 --> 11:19.332
No, Sergeant!

11:19.334 --> 11:22.168
Eyes front, Marine.

11:22.170 --> 11:24.804
Sergeant.

11:28.042 --> 11:30.843
Take a good look, marines.

11:30.845 --> 11:33.313
This is what war is.

11:33.315 --> 11:37.417
You follow my orders,
you just make it out of here alive.

11:37.419 --> 11:39.352
There's no second
chances out here.

11:39.354 --> 11:41.421
We either win or we die.

11:41.423 --> 11:42.955
Understand?!

11:42.957 --> 11:43.956
Yes, Sergeant!

11:43.958 --> 11:45.224
Now fall out!

11:45.226 --> 11:48.294
Dave Rossi.

11:48.296 --> 11:50.296
It's been a while.

11:50.298 --> 11:52.982
Too long.

11:52.984 --> 11:55.401
How did you know
it was me?

11:55.403 --> 11:58.187
Recognized you
from your book cover.

11:58.189 --> 12:00.473
You read my books?

12:00.475 --> 12:03.242
I thumbed through
one or two.

12:03.244 --> 12:06.195
I didn't know
you were out here.

12:06.197 --> 12:11.034
Yeah, I figured I'd get me
some of those California girls.

12:11.036 --> 12:12.535
And did you?

12:12.537 --> 12:14.037
Once or twice.

12:14.039 --> 12:17.840
But after my last divorce,
I figured, uh,

12:17.842 --> 12:20.293
marriage just wasn't
my thing.

12:20.295 --> 12:22.879
Yeah, tell me about it.

12:23.830 --> 12:25.598
It's good seeing you.

12:26.600 --> 12:28.301
I got to go.

12:28.303 --> 12:30.386
No, no. Let me give you
my card.

12:30.388 --> 12:33.056
I can't believe
I ran into you like this.

12:33.058 --> 12:37.360
Look, we gotta
get together. You could--

12:51.375 --> 12:53.459
Hey, man--
hey, whoa.

12:53.461 --> 12:54.660
Easy, buddy.

12:54.662 --> 12:56.796
Just want to see if
you'd like a portrait.

12:56.798 --> 12:58.498
Already got it started.

12:58.500 --> 13:00.216
See?

13:02.636 --> 13:04.837
It looks just like you.

13:06.474 --> 13:08.057
No.

13:30.426 --> 13:31.726
If Lindsay
was a transient,

13:31.764 --> 13:34.098
it makes sense that the
other victims could be, too.

13:34.100 --> 13:37.618
This area of Santa Monica
has a heavy homeless population.

13:40.121 --> 13:43.507
That explains why Garcia
had trouble matching dental records.

13:43.509 --> 13:45.626
Regular office visits
aren't a priority

13:45.628 --> 13:47.962
for people who live
on the streets.

13:47.964 --> 13:50.147
He's been shaven clean
and left exposed.

13:50.149 --> 13:52.516
This is a complete
change in M.O.

13:52.518 --> 13:54.635
Yeah, and look at his skin.

13:54.637 --> 13:56.753
It looks like chemical burns.

13:56.755 --> 13:58.088
It smells like bleach.

13:58.090 --> 14:00.107
That's an evolution,
but why?

14:00.109 --> 14:01.592
Was the fire drawing
too much attention,

14:01.594 --> 14:04.928
or does the chemical burn
fulfill another purpose?

14:04.930 --> 14:07.264
He's got ligature marks
on his wrists.

14:07.266 --> 14:09.600
He couldn't fight back
while the unsub burned him.

14:09.602 --> 14:11.101
Changed his dumping
ground, too.

14:11.103 --> 14:13.103
In sight of a homeless
shelter?

14:13.105 --> 14:15.372
If he wasn't clear before,
he certainly is now.

14:15.374 --> 14:16.874
His face and prints
are intact.

14:16.876 --> 14:19.660
We should be able to I.D.
him faster than the others.

14:19.662 --> 14:21.078
Maybe that's intentional.

14:21.080 --> 14:23.414
His name's Jeremy.

14:24.966 --> 14:27.251
Give me a second.

14:28.586 --> 14:30.220
Excuse me.

14:31.156 --> 14:33.223
Please.

14:40.198 --> 14:42.399
You recognize him?

14:42.401 --> 14:45.819
He worked the Boardwalk.

14:45.821 --> 14:47.938
He was a artist.

14:47.940 --> 14:50.240
You sure?

14:50.242 --> 14:51.659
Thank you.

14:51.661 --> 14:53.694
This helps.

15:03.872 --> 15:04.922
Look--

15:04.924 --> 15:06.373
You don't have to say it.

15:06.375 --> 15:08.342
It depends on what
I was gonna say.

15:08.344 --> 15:12.546
You were going to apologize for
walking away yesterday. Don't.

15:12.548 --> 15:15.599
Last time I saw you,
you were unconscious,

15:15.601 --> 15:18.302
on your way home
with a concussion

15:18.304 --> 15:20.971
and a shrapnel wound
in your arm.

15:20.973 --> 15:23.891
I've still got the scar.

15:23.893 --> 15:25.609
What happened?

15:28.146 --> 15:31.615
You remember Danny James,

15:31.617 --> 15:34.902
PFC from Iowa,
was 19 years old?

15:34.904 --> 15:37.738
You remember what they
did to him over there?

15:37.740 --> 15:40.741
He was captured
outside Hue, I think.

15:40.743 --> 15:43.577
They held him
for 3 nights.

15:43.579 --> 15:46.497
No eyes. No ears.

15:46.499 --> 15:48.582
No arms.

15:48.584 --> 15:50.751
But he was still alive.

15:50.753 --> 15:54.254
You remember why
they did that to him?

15:54.256 --> 15:57.091
Hell, you were the first
one to figure it out.

15:57.093 --> 16:00.594
Fear. They were trying
to scare us.

16:00.596 --> 16:04.014
Same thing's happening here.

16:05.400 --> 16:09.886
Now, these people
are here to help us.

16:09.888 --> 16:13.891
They got work to do,
so everybody listen up.

16:13.893 --> 16:17.411
The guy we're looking for
is hunting the homeless.

16:17.413 --> 16:19.580
He seems to be
most active at night.

16:19.582 --> 16:21.898
We believe that this
unknown subject, or unsub,

16:21.900 --> 16:24.284
is trying to make a social
or a political statement

16:24.286 --> 16:25.902
by targeting
the homeless community.

16:25.904 --> 16:28.172
He's evolved from obliterating
his victims with fire

16:28.174 --> 16:29.590
to wanting them
to be identified

16:29.592 --> 16:31.341
while still
depersonalizing them.

16:31.343 --> 16:33.544
Listen, this guy's
burning people with bleach.

16:33.546 --> 16:35.095
He's trying to scare you.

16:35.097 --> 16:37.548
And the shaving of
the heads is most likely

16:37.550 --> 16:40.117
another way he can
humiliate his victims.

16:40.119 --> 16:42.419
This unsub has a method
of transportation

16:42.421 --> 16:45.322
and the facilities to bleach
and burn his victims.

16:45.324 --> 16:47.941
He dumps the bodies prior
to the morning commute,

16:47.943 --> 16:49.476
so he could have
a day job.

16:49.478 --> 16:51.028
You need to be
hypervigilant

16:51.030 --> 16:52.529
and look after
one another.

16:52.531 --> 16:55.732
Sleep in groups
and in shifts.

16:55.734 --> 16:57.267
How will we know
it's him?

16:57.269 --> 16:58.435
You might not.

16:58.437 --> 17:00.270
This guy blends in.

17:00.272 --> 17:01.805
He's probably a local,

17:01.807 --> 17:04.540
someone who feels wronged
by members of your community.

17:04.542 --> 17:06.577
He does not draw
attention to himself,

17:06.579 --> 17:08.212
and he's meticulous
in his planning.

17:08.214 --> 17:10.414
The fact that he's now dumping
the bodies away from the pier

17:10.415 --> 17:12.883
means he's probably aware
of our investigation

17:12.885 --> 17:14.718
and that this is far
from over.

17:14.720 --> 17:17.588
We need to increase the police
presence on the street.

17:17.589 --> 17:20.790
This guy is smart.
We have to be smarter.

17:22.560 --> 17:24.595
Thanks for your help today.

17:24.597 --> 17:27.964
We couldn't have reached out
like this on our own.

17:27.967 --> 17:30.134
These people trust you.

17:30.136 --> 17:31.468
Your training paid off.

17:31.470 --> 17:32.803
Thanks to you.

17:32.805 --> 17:35.072
I did my job.

17:35.074 --> 17:37.274
No, you did
a lot more than that.

17:37.276 --> 17:39.943
I was a screw-up
and you knew it.

17:39.945 --> 17:44.915
Well, maybe at first,
but you showed potential.

17:47.318 --> 17:51.205
Fall back! Fall back!

17:51.207 --> 17:52.739
Fall back! Fall back now!

17:52.741 --> 17:54.541
Fall back, marines!
Fall back!

17:54.543 --> 17:56.860
That's an order!
Fall back!

17:56.862 --> 17:58.662
Fall back!

17:58.664 --> 18:01.431
Aah!
Uhh!

18:04.286 --> 18:05.519
Hernandez!

18:05.521 --> 18:07.354
Take cover, Rossi!
Pull back! That's an order!

18:09.524 --> 18:11.525
But what about Hernandez?

18:16.414 --> 18:17.648
Leave no man behind,
Sergeant!

18:17.650 --> 18:20.551
Pull back! That's an order!

18:20.553 --> 18:24.721
Rossi, you cover this position
and cover Hernandez!

18:24.723 --> 18:26.623
I don't know if I can,
Sergeant!

18:26.625 --> 18:29.126
You can and you will.

18:29.128 --> 18:31.461
Where are you going?! Wait!

18:31.463 --> 18:34.164
Sergeant! Sergeant!

19:16.391 --> 19:19.109
Look, we're staying
just a few blocks from here.

19:19.111 --> 19:20.961
Why don't you come back
with me?

19:20.963 --> 19:22.579
I can get you a room.

19:22.581 --> 19:24.915
This is my home, David.

19:24.917 --> 19:27.651
This is no way
for a war hero to live.

19:27.653 --> 19:31.555
You know how many veterans
are on the street?

19:31.557 --> 19:34.090
Too many.

19:34.092 --> 19:36.593
More every day.

19:36.595 --> 19:40.930
It's not glamorous,
but... it's me.

19:42.116 --> 19:44.568
No, it's not.

19:44.570 --> 19:48.739
You think after 40 years,
you know a damn thing about me?

19:48.741 --> 19:52.409
How long have you
lived like this?

19:52.411 --> 19:54.494
I worked construction
for a while,

19:54.496 --> 19:57.214
but no one wants
an old man on the job

19:57.216 --> 20:00.283
when they can get somebody
younger and cheaper.

20:00.285 --> 20:02.386
How long?

20:02.388 --> 20:04.721
A year.

20:05.673 --> 20:08.458
Maybe 5.

20:08.460 --> 20:12.062
It's hard to keep track
without a watch.

20:12.064 --> 20:14.514
Then let me help you.

20:16.834 --> 20:19.803
If I had wanted your help,

20:19.805 --> 20:23.440
I would have asked for it.

20:38.923 --> 20:41.361
Could the fire have
destroyed evidence of bleach

20:41.386 --> 20:42.794
on the previous victims?

20:42.795 --> 20:45.212
Chemical residue would have
turned up in the autopsies.

20:45.214 --> 20:48.515
So we were right. He changed M.O.
to perfect his message.

20:48.517 --> 20:50.350
He changed something
else, too.

20:50.352 --> 20:52.302
I found bleach
in Jeremy's lungs.

20:52.304 --> 20:54.304
The unsub drowned him.

20:54.306 --> 20:58.174
The first victims
were incinerated postmortem.

20:58.176 --> 21:00.444
Why torture now?

21:00.446 --> 21:02.779
He's starting to enjoy
the kills.

21:02.781 --> 21:04.865
So as he fine-tunes
his methodology,

21:04.867 --> 21:07.484
he's also fine-tuning
what gets him off.

21:07.486 --> 21:10.287
Well, he managed to bleach
Jeremy inside and out.

21:10.289 --> 21:12.789
This could be about cleanliness.

21:12.791 --> 21:14.408
Or cleansing.

21:14.410 --> 21:16.243
The socioeconomic kind.

21:16.245 --> 21:18.962
He's trying to eradicate
the homeless.

21:35.880 --> 21:36.980
Need a blanket?

21:36.982 --> 21:38.765
Thanks, I've got one
that's all right.

21:38.767 --> 21:41.485
If you want to, check with some of
the younger kids first.

21:41.487 --> 21:43.687
Already taken care of.
Why don't you come with me?

21:43.689 --> 21:45.722
I can give you a shower
and a warm bed.

21:45.724 --> 21:48.057
I'm not a prostitute.

21:48.059 --> 21:49.659
I didn't say you were.

21:49.661 --> 21:53.363
I just thought I could
help you with your problem.

21:53.365 --> 21:55.031
And what is my problem?

21:55.033 --> 21:56.032
Your disease.

21:56.034 --> 21:57.117
Don't have a disease.

21:57.119 --> 21:58.452
- Yes, you do.
- No, I don't!

21:58.454 --> 22:00.504
I'm going to rid you of it
once and for all.

22:00.506 --> 22:02.205
Leave her alone!

22:24.479 --> 22:27.731
No! Let me go! Help!

22:55.725 --> 22:57.392
Did you find her?

22:57.394 --> 22:59.427
Not yet.

22:59.429 --> 23:02.097
I had that son of a bitch
right in my hands,

23:02.099 --> 23:03.515
I let him get away!

23:03.517 --> 23:06.902
A few less drinks
might have helped.

23:06.904 --> 23:10.689
What the hell
are you talking about?

23:10.691 --> 23:14.442
I think saying age put you
on the streets is a copout.

23:15.912 --> 23:18.830
Don't you lecture me,
Rossi.

23:18.832 --> 23:20.949
What did booze cost you first?

23:20.951 --> 23:24.169
Your home? Your job?
Or maybe one of your wives.

23:24.171 --> 23:25.987
This wasn't my fault!

23:25.989 --> 23:27.856
I'm not saying that it was.

23:27.858 --> 23:30.458
I tried to save Sarah!
I couldn't!

23:30.460 --> 23:32.160
So now you're giving up.

23:32.162 --> 23:34.379
There's nothing else
I can do.

23:34.381 --> 23:36.497
Yes, there is.

23:36.499 --> 23:39.718
Help me to help her.

23:44.056 --> 23:47.842
Now, I want you to relax

23:47.844 --> 23:49.844
and focus.

23:49.846 --> 23:51.029
What's the point of this?

23:51.031 --> 23:52.230
I told you.

23:52.232 --> 23:54.449
It's a cognitive interview.

23:54.451 --> 23:56.701
Many times our subconscious
picks up on details

23:56.703 --> 23:58.853
our conscious mind's
not aware of.

23:58.855 --> 24:01.022
A marine more so.

24:01.024 --> 24:03.909
It's been a long time
since I was active, Dave.

24:03.911 --> 24:06.545
The instinct never goes away.

24:06.547 --> 24:08.046
Now, close your eyes.

24:08.048 --> 24:09.331
Oh, yes, sir.

24:09.333 --> 24:11.750
Take yourself back
to that night.

24:11.752 --> 24:13.534
Put yourself in the alley.

24:13.536 --> 24:14.869
It's dark.

24:14.871 --> 24:17.339
You're getting ready for bed.

24:17.341 --> 24:19.874
Something caught
your attention.

24:19.876 --> 24:21.026
What is it?

24:21.028 --> 24:22.543
And what is my problem?

24:22.545 --> 24:24.429
Sarah's voice.

24:24.431 --> 24:29.150
All right. But you must have
heard her voice a hundred times.

24:29.152 --> 24:31.403
What made it stick out?

24:31.405 --> 24:32.554
Don't have a disease.

24:32.556 --> 24:34.239
She's afraid.

24:34.241 --> 24:36.508
Can you see why?

24:38.394 --> 24:39.560
All right,
what else stuck out?

24:39.562 --> 24:41.863
Any distinctive odors?

24:47.569 --> 24:50.405
I'm not sure.

24:53.742 --> 24:55.894
It smells like a hospital.

24:55.896 --> 24:59.214
Whatever it is,
it's out of place.

24:59.216 --> 25:00.599
Focus on that smell.

25:00.601 --> 25:03.251
Let it draw you
into the conversation.

25:03.253 --> 25:04.469
...blanket?

25:04.471 --> 25:06.221
Thanks, I've got one
that's all right.

25:06.223 --> 25:08.473
If you want to, check with
some of the younger kids.

25:08.475 --> 25:09.474
I see him.

25:09.476 --> 25:10.809
Describe him to me.

25:10.811 --> 25:12.010
Why don't you come with me?

25:12.012 --> 25:13.695
I--I can't make him out.

25:13.697 --> 25:15.063
He's standing in the shadows.

25:15.065 --> 25:18.116
Blue collar? Clean-cut?

25:18.118 --> 25:20.819
Jeans and a button-down shirt.

25:20.821 --> 25:23.104
Can you see his face?

25:23.106 --> 25:24.372
It's too dark.

25:24.374 --> 25:26.541
Ok, let's go back
to the clothes.

25:26.543 --> 25:27.659
We follow them down

25:27.661 --> 25:30.445
to his hands.
Is he wearing a wedding ring?

25:30.447 --> 25:32.914
He's wearing gloves.

25:32.916 --> 25:35.450
Medical gloves?
Work gloves?

25:35.452 --> 25:37.168
Driving gloves.

25:37.170 --> 25:39.587
Are there any other
distinctive smells?

25:39.589 --> 25:42.140
Did he leave
his car running?

25:42.142 --> 25:44.392
Gasoline.

25:44.394 --> 25:47.195
Older model Ford.

25:47.197 --> 25:49.597
Yeah, the engine
is still running.

25:49.599 --> 25:51.566
It's a Mustang, I think.

25:51.568 --> 25:53.068
Can you see
the license plate?

25:53.070 --> 25:55.020
I'm lying on the ground.

25:55.022 --> 25:58.573
He's--he's taking her
to the car!

25:58.575 --> 26:00.608
He's coming right at me!

26:00.610 --> 26:02.977
The plate is right in front of you!
Tell me what it says.

26:02.979 --> 26:04.145
I can't see it.

26:04.147 --> 26:05.413
Yes, you can.
You can do this.

26:05.415 --> 26:07.449
- "J"!
- Yeah, go ahead.

26:07.451 --> 26:08.750
"W"!

26:08.752 --> 26:09.784
Go on! Go on!

26:09.786 --> 26:11.319
"D"!

26:11.321 --> 26:14.122
That's all I got.

26:15.458 --> 26:17.792
Rossi...

26:18.678 --> 26:20.845
You gotta find her.

26:20.847 --> 26:23.682
I can't lose another one.

26:23.684 --> 26:26.134
Another one?

26:28.804 --> 26:30.722
Try and get some rest.

26:33.092 --> 26:35.110
Factoring in a 2-mile
comfort zone

26:35.112 --> 26:37.529
mixed with Mustang
registries

26:37.531 --> 26:40.014
and a JWD partial,

26:40.016 --> 26:41.449
I come up with squat.

26:41.451 --> 26:43.952
He probably stole
the plates, Garcia.

26:43.954 --> 26:45.403
Run Mustang registries
from that area

26:45.405 --> 26:49.023
and focus on the ones
manufactured prior to the 1980s.

26:49.025 --> 26:51.626
Uh, I've got 10 possibilities.

26:51.628 --> 26:54.195
Well, I doubt this guy
could maintain a steady relationship.

26:54.197 --> 26:56.581
Eliminate any vehicles
registered to women.

26:59.001 --> 27:01.586
Only knocks off 2.
We got 8 more to go, folks.

27:01.588 --> 27:03.004
All right, what are
their occupations?

27:03.006 --> 27:04.305
Uh, ad exec,

27:04.307 --> 27:05.840
a teacher, a waiter...

27:05.842 --> 27:07.509
Whoa, I got a firefighter.

27:07.511 --> 27:10.261
Well, that would definitely
explain this guy's proficiency at burning.

27:10.263 --> 27:12.597
And he would know the layout of
the street cameras to avoid detection.

27:12.599 --> 27:14.096
Garcia, does this firefighter
have any relationship

27:14.121 --> 27:15.568
to the homeless community?

27:15.569 --> 27:16.985
Let's see...

27:23.559 --> 27:26.361
Chad Mills--third generation
firefighter.

27:26.363 --> 27:28.830
He saved 6 homeless people
from an electrical fire

27:28.832 --> 27:31.032
that destroyed the warehouse
they were squatting in.

27:31.034 --> 27:32.400
9 others died in the blaze.

27:32.402 --> 27:34.035
That's not a coincidence.

27:34.037 --> 27:36.020
Why didn't he come up in
the search of first responders.

27:36.022 --> 27:37.055
Because he isn't one
anymore.

27:37.057 --> 27:40.458
He left the department
two months ago.

27:40.460 --> 27:42.394
Just before
the murders started.

27:42.396 --> 27:44.512
Garcia--
sending you his address now.

28:26.839 --> 28:28.807
Unh! Unh!

28:56.585 --> 28:57.785
Clear!

28:57.787 --> 28:59.120
He was just here.

28:59.122 --> 29:00.355
I need medical.

29:00.357 --> 29:02.624
I'm going around back.

29:02.626 --> 29:04.325
He couldn't
have gotten far.

29:04.327 --> 29:05.677
Let's go.

29:16.172 --> 29:18.172
Try not to talk, Sarah.

29:18.174 --> 29:19.974
Help's on the way.

29:19.976 --> 29:23.695
This will coat your throat
and help dilute the bleach.

29:34.723 --> 29:35.690
Get in!

29:35.692 --> 29:37.158
What's the status on Mills?

29:37.160 --> 29:38.910
Mills is missing.
We don't have him.

29:38.912 --> 29:41.362
I repeat, Mills is gone.

30:15.948 --> 30:17.782
Uhh... Unh!

30:17.784 --> 30:19.233
You ruined everything.

30:19.235 --> 30:20.535
Come on.

30:35.348 --> 30:36.899
I should have
seen this coming.

30:36.901 --> 30:39.401
Rossi, you couldn't have known
he'd circle back for Scott.

30:39.923 --> 30:40.533
What you need?

30:40.534 --> 30:44.369
Garcia, give us everything
you have on Chad Mills.

30:54.095 --> 30:55.412
No dust.

30:55.414 --> 30:56.964
Nothing out of sorts.

30:56.966 --> 30:59.216
His clothes are organized
by color.

31:01.520 --> 31:05.639
You know, this speaks
to clear signs of OCD behavior.

31:05.641 --> 31:07.925
Sarah had some sort
of gel in her hair.

31:07.927 --> 31:10.394
I want to try to find
the source.

31:11.363 --> 31:12.646
What is it?

31:12.648 --> 31:14.865
Quell, a medical-grade
disinfectant.

31:14.867 --> 31:18.369
His OCD may manifest
in extreme germaphobia.

31:18.371 --> 31:20.538
That must be why
he shaved Jeremy's head.

31:20.540 --> 31:22.957
There wasn't any sign
of disinfectant until today, though.

31:22.959 --> 31:25.776
But it might have been eliminated
by the bleach and the fire.

31:25.778 --> 31:29.413
Guys, fire, bleach, quell--
these are all forms of sterilization.

31:29.415 --> 31:31.265
So you think the burning
might be incidental?

31:31.267 --> 31:33.250
If he's socioeconomically
cleansing the streets,

31:33.252 --> 31:34.656
he could be treating
the homeless population

31:34.681 --> 31:36.455
like an infection.

31:36.556 --> 31:37.972
To him they're a virus.

31:37.974 --> 31:40.123
And he's the cure.

31:40.125 --> 31:41.725
I figured out why Mills
left the fire department.

31:41.727 --> 31:43.777
He was forced out
because he contracted

31:43.779 --> 31:45.796
a drug-resistant
strain of tuberculosis.

31:45.798 --> 31:47.348
How did he get it,
you ask?

31:47.350 --> 31:48.895
Two of the squatters he saved

31:48.920 --> 31:50.635
from that burning warehouse
were infected.

31:50.636 --> 31:53.938
Theory is he caught it through
close, unprotected contact.

31:53.940 --> 31:55.272
That's a hell of a trigger.

31:55.274 --> 31:56.824
He blames the homeless
community for getting him sick.

31:56.826 --> 31:59.693
Combine that trauma with an
OCD germaphobe and what do you get?

31:59.695 --> 32:02.145
A serial killer who thinks
he can stop the spread of TB

32:02.147 --> 32:03.647
by killing
an entire population.

32:03.649 --> 32:05.649
The same way the victims
of the plague were burned.

32:05.651 --> 32:07.317
Well, now he's on the run
and he can't go back home,

32:07.319 --> 32:08.652
so where
would he take Scott?

32:08.654 --> 32:11.372
Back to where
his trauma originated.

32:11.374 --> 32:13.757
Garcia, give us the address
of the warehouse fire.

32:19.831 --> 32:22.332
Careful.
You gonna get me wet.

32:22.334 --> 32:24.184
I'm gonna burn you alive.

32:24.186 --> 32:26.503
That's a first for me.

32:26.505 --> 32:29.023
Don't go out of your way
on my account.

32:29.025 --> 32:30.858
You ruined my mission.

32:30.860 --> 32:33.343
Your mission?

32:33.345 --> 32:36.513
You fightin'
the wrong war, son.

32:36.515 --> 32:38.983
I am not your son!

32:38.985 --> 32:40.868
That the best you got?

32:44.857 --> 32:47.575
What's the matter?
You sick?

32:50.194 --> 32:52.496
You should recognize
the signs.

32:52.498 --> 32:54.415
It was your kind
who did this to me.

32:54.417 --> 32:56.417
My kind?

32:56.419 --> 32:57.868
Yeah.

33:00.505 --> 33:03.206
I was going to matter.

33:04.225 --> 33:06.343
You still can, Chad.

33:06.345 --> 33:09.212
Come any closer
and I burn him.

33:09.214 --> 33:11.315
You don't want
to do that.

33:11.317 --> 33:12.516
And you don't want to shoot.

33:12.518 --> 33:13.684
Otherwise we'll both go up.

33:13.686 --> 33:15.653
That's pretty brave
what you did,

33:15.655 --> 33:18.022
running into that fire
on your own.

33:18.024 --> 33:20.557
Yeah? Look how that turned out.

33:20.559 --> 33:23.393
I don't know, if you ask me,
I say it was pretty stupid.

33:23.395 --> 33:25.112
- Stupid?
- Yeah, that's right.

33:25.114 --> 33:26.997
You went in without
protective gear.

33:26.999 --> 33:28.782
Looks like maybe you were
trying to prove something.

33:28.784 --> 33:31.085
Third-generation fireman.
What's there to prove?

33:31.087 --> 33:32.069
It's in his genes.

33:32.071 --> 33:34.588
Quite a legacy
to try to live up to.

33:34.590 --> 33:36.757
But you just wanted to be
the best, didn't you.

33:36.759 --> 33:37.841
I am the best!

33:37.843 --> 33:39.510
Guess we'll never know
for sure.

33:39.512 --> 33:42.046
My whole life, I knew
I was gonna be a fireman.

33:42.048 --> 33:43.180
That I would matter!

33:43.182 --> 33:45.432
You do matter, Chad.
Everyone matters.

33:45.434 --> 33:47.134
Not him! He doesn't.

33:47.136 --> 33:48.686
That man is a marine.

33:48.688 --> 33:50.471
He risked his life
to protect us.

33:50.473 --> 33:51.939
You telling me
that doesn't matter?

33:51.941 --> 33:54.058
He's right, Dave.

33:54.060 --> 33:56.110
What?

33:56.112 --> 33:57.695
He drops that lighter,

33:57.697 --> 34:00.263
this whole place
goes up in flames.

34:00.265 --> 34:03.283
I don't want y'all caught
in the crossfire because of me.

34:03.285 --> 34:05.619
It's time to fall back.

34:05.621 --> 34:07.788
I'm not leaving you
behind.

34:07.790 --> 34:09.606
That's an order, Marine!

34:17.916 --> 34:20.784
Ok, we're falling back.

34:39.469 --> 34:41.938
What you gonna do now?

34:44.943 --> 34:47.911
Guess it's time
to finish this.

34:47.913 --> 34:51.281
You're not getting out
of this place alive.

34:51.283 --> 34:53.784
I didn't say I was.

34:53.786 --> 34:56.754
Do I get any last words?

34:56.755 --> 35:00.991
No one wants to hear them
'cause no one cares if you die.

35:00.993 --> 35:02.659
That's where you're wrong.

35:02.661 --> 35:05.796
What are you doing?
I'm gonna burn this place down!

35:13.104 --> 35:15.139
Don't do it!

35:37.912 --> 35:39.997
Thank you.

35:42.700 --> 35:46.637
So, that was quite
a stunt you pulled in there.

35:46.639 --> 35:49.506
I knew you'd get
the message.

35:49.508 --> 35:54.344
Figured that was my best chance
not to go down with him.

35:54.346 --> 35:57.481
So you bet your life
on the BAU.

35:57.483 --> 36:00.851
I bet my life on you.

36:00.853 --> 36:03.437
Do you know why
I joined the FBI?

36:03.439 --> 36:05.239
If you say--

36:05.241 --> 36:06.740
Because of you.

36:06.742 --> 36:10.277
You could say
the Corps changed me,

36:10.279 --> 36:11.862
or the war.

36:11.864 --> 36:15.949
But it was you
who made me honest.

36:15.951 --> 36:21.421
So, please,
be honest with me now.

36:21.423 --> 36:24.241
What are you running from?

36:28.046 --> 36:32.182
You remember how you got
that scar in the first place?

36:32.184 --> 36:33.617
Of course I do.

36:37.589 --> 36:39.439
Perez,
cover our right flank.

36:39.441 --> 36:41.592
Hernandez, our left.

36:41.594 --> 36:43.927
Mattheson,
I need you on point.

36:54.205 --> 36:55.739
Damn.

36:55.741 --> 36:57.991
Everyone, stand back!

37:00.411 --> 37:02.112
How bad, Sergeant?

37:02.114 --> 37:04.429
Hernandez, I need you
to take the troops back

37:04.454 --> 37:05.617
to our last position.

37:05.618 --> 37:06.917
Sergeant?

37:06.919 --> 37:09.469
Any movement
and this whole field lights up.

37:09.471 --> 37:11.138
Now move the men back.

37:11.140 --> 37:13.123
Yes, Sergeant.

37:13.125 --> 37:16.493
You better go, too, Sergeant.

37:16.495 --> 37:18.812
Can't do that, son.

37:18.814 --> 37:21.014
Leave no one behind.

37:21.016 --> 37:22.633
Don't die 'cause if screwed up.

37:22.635 --> 37:24.301
Who said anything
about dying?

37:24.303 --> 37:26.970
We're at the end
of the chain.

37:26.972 --> 37:28.672
We can use that ditch
for cover.

37:28.674 --> 37:30.340
We'll never make it.

37:30.342 --> 37:32.475
On my count.

37:32.477 --> 37:35.445
3...

37:35.447 --> 37:37.848
2...

37:39.701 --> 37:40.984
1!

37:44.923 --> 37:47.324
That blast
gave you a concussion.

37:47.326 --> 37:49.126
When you regained
consciousness,

37:49.128 --> 37:51.962
you were already
on your way home.

37:51.964 --> 37:54.932
Next thing I knew,
I was in the hospital

37:54.934 --> 37:57.768
getting ready
to rotate home.

37:57.770 --> 38:00.854
And I was receiving
a commendation

38:00.856 --> 38:04.174
for heroic bravery.
Huh.

38:04.176 --> 38:06.693
And you deserved it.

38:06.695 --> 38:10.197
Not a lot of people
would have done that.

38:10.199 --> 38:11.732
No.

38:11.734 --> 38:15.602
But someone did more.

38:15.604 --> 38:17.906
Hernandez, I need you
to take the troops back

38:17.931 --> 38:19.207
to our last position.

38:19.208 --> 38:20.624
Sergeant?

38:20.626 --> 38:23.493
Any movement
and this whole field lights up.

38:23.495 --> 38:25.829
Now move the men back.

38:25.831 --> 38:27.247
Yes, Sergeant.

38:33.004 --> 38:35.022
Hernandez, what are you doing?

38:35.024 --> 38:37.040
Push 'em through.
I got work to do.

38:39.711 --> 38:42.012
On my count.
We'll never make it.

38:42.014 --> 38:44.381
3...

38:44.383 --> 38:46.049
2...

38:49.821 --> 38:50.988
1!

38:55.226 --> 38:57.928
Aah!

39:00.548 --> 39:02.249
Hernandez?

39:03.901 --> 39:05.285
But why?

39:05.287 --> 39:07.537
Why did he do it?

39:07.539 --> 39:10.123
Or why did
I take credit?

39:10.125 --> 39:11.925
Both.

39:13.461 --> 39:16.263
The short answer is...

39:16.265 --> 39:18.765
I was ordered to.

39:18.767 --> 39:23.586
We were fighting that
P.R. war back home.

39:23.588 --> 39:26.723
The government
needed a face,

39:26.725 --> 39:29.776
a living face,
to parade around,

39:29.778 --> 39:34.147
to solicit support
for a unpopular war.

39:35.483 --> 39:37.951
I was chosen.

39:37.953 --> 39:40.287
And Hernandez?

39:40.289 --> 39:43.824
He was paying a debt.

39:45.243 --> 39:48.412
He was being a marine.

39:48.414 --> 39:52.799
He died
so that we could live.

39:55.303 --> 39:57.454
And you couldn't tell anyone.

40:04.979 --> 40:06.646
Come with me.

40:06.648 --> 40:08.598
Where?

40:08.600 --> 40:11.401
To honor our dead.

40:21.579 --> 40:24.748
"I am not concerned
that you have fallen.

40:24.750 --> 40:27.868
I am concerned
that you will rise."

40:27.870 --> 40:29.703
Abraham Lincoln.

40:32.173 --> 40:35.158
Your grandfather
was a hero, son.

40:35.160 --> 40:36.993
Thank you, sir.

40:36.995 --> 40:39.463
He saved both of our lives.

41:01.619 --> 41:05.572
You know, it's time you let yourself
off the hook, Sergeant.

41:05.574 --> 41:07.324
You did your duty.

41:07.326 --> 41:10.127
This country owes you
for your service.

41:10.129 --> 41:11.878
Oh, no. It doesn't
owe me anything.

41:11.880 --> 41:14.381
I had a feeling
you'd say that.

41:15.666 --> 41:18.368
But they're gonna
help you anyway.

41:18.370 --> 41:19.886
You know what this place is?

41:19.888 --> 41:22.806
It's called New Directions.

41:22.808 --> 41:24.836
It's an outreach center
dedicated to help vets

41:24.861 --> 41:26.861
land on their feet.

41:28.396 --> 41:30.514
Welcome home, Marine.

41:32.817 --> 41:35.068
Semper Fi.

41:36.720 --> 41:38.572
Hoo-rah.

41:38.574 --> 41:43.574
